
---- Function and ESC keys ------------------------------------------

     The default keys for navigation are function keys.  However, if
     your keyboard does not have functions keys, or you are running 
     across a TIP line, you must use ESC key sequences.

     > To activate ESC keys for navigation, press the ESC key once; 
       when you exit Help and return to main screens, you'll see the 
       legend at the bottom shows the ESC keys to use for navigation

     > To change the navigation legend on the main screen back to
       show function keys, press the ESC key once, then press the
       letter "f" key once.

     > To use ESC key navigation (for example, ESC-2), press the ESC
       key once, then press the number key.


---- Return and Enter ---------------------------------------------

     > Use Return or Enter to mark options in menus



---- Summary of navigation ----------------------------------------
 
     > Main Screens

       ESC       ............. activate/show ESC key legend
       ESC-f     ............. activate/show Function key legend
       F2, ESC-2 ............. continue to next screen
       F4, ESC-4 ............. change information entered
       F6, ESC-6 ............. access help
       Control-N, down arrow . move down in menu
       Control-P, up arrow ... move up in menu
       Control-H ............. back space in field
       Control-U ............. back space in field
       Back Space key ........ back space in field
       Arrow keys ............ highlight option in menu
       Return  ........ ...... mark option in menu
       

     > Help Screens
        
       F2, ESC-2 = go to (option selected)
       F3, ESC-3 = go to Help Subjects or Help Main Index
       F5, ESC-5 = exit help

     > To use Control key navigation (for example, Control-U), hold
       down the Control key and simultaneously press the letter key.

     > To use ESC key navigation (for example, ESC-2), hold down the 
       ESC key and simultaneously press the number key.
  

---- Text fields ----------------------------------------------------

     > To enter information, start typing at the cursor

     > To validate and commit data, press Return 

     > To move from field-to-field use:

       Up arrow or Control-P
       Down arrow or Control-N    

     > To erase a current value, use one of the following:

       Back Space key
       Control-H
       Control-U


---- Menus -----------------------------------------------------------

     > To highlight an item you want to select, use the arrow keys

     > To select an item [X], press Return
         
     > To deselect an item [ ], use the arrow keys to move to 
       another field and press Return


---- Screens ---------------------------------------------------------

     > To change information on confirmation screens, choose F4 or 
       ESC-4

     > To access Help, choose F6 or ESC-6

     > To exit the Solaris installation program, choose F5 or ESC-5

     > To advance to the next screen, choose F2 or ESC-2

     > To get back to a confirmation screen you've already passed, 
       press the F2 key to continue to that screen. 


---- Help Screens ----------------------------------------------------
  
     > To exit help and return to the screen you left, choose F5 or
       ESC-5

     > To select a help subject, use the arrow keys to highlight the 
       option, and press Return to mark it [X]

     > To go to the subject you've selected, choose F2 or ESC-2

     > To go to the Help Main Index, choose F3 or ESC-3
